SIMPLE: ogee
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ogee
<hw>O*gee"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>ogive</ets>,
<ets>augive</ets>, LL. <ets>augiva</ets>, of uncertain origin; cf.LL.
<ets>ogis</ets> a support, prop. L. <ets>augere</ets> to increase,
strengthen, Sp. <ets>auge</ets> highest point of power or fortune,
apogee, Ar. <ets>auj</ets>, an astronomical term.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>A molding, the section of which
is the form of the letter S, with the convex part above; cyma reversa.
See <xex>Illust.</xex> under <er>Cyma</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence, any similar figure used for any
purpose.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Ogee arch</b></col> <fld>(Arch.)</fld>, <cd>a pointed
arch, each of the sides of which has the curve of an ogee, that is, has
a reversed curve near the apex.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ogeechee lime</ent>⟦br⟧
